Câu 9: 
When does the testing process stops? 
A. Testing never ends 
B. When resources (time and budget) are over 
C. When some coverage is reached 
D. When quality criterion is reached
Copilot said:
Copilot

The correct answer is D. When quality criterion is reached.

Testing typically stops when the predefined quality criteria are met, ensuring that the software is of acceptable quality and ready for release. This criterion can include factors like the number of open defects, test coverage, and performance benchmarks.
